WEBVTT

1
00:00:13.278 --> 00:00:16.070
When we're young, we're innocently brave,
我们年轻时就像初生牛犊，

2
00:00:16.112 --> 00:00:19.629
and we fearlessly dream about what our lives might be like.
无畏地梦想着 我们的人生可能会是什么样。

3
00:00:19.653 --> 00:00:23.171
Maybe you wanted to be an astronaut or a rocket scientist.
或许你想成为宇航员 或是火箭科学家。

4
00:00:23.195 --> 00:00:26.963
Maybe you dreamed of traveling to every continent.
或许你的梦想是 环游世界的旅行。

5
00:00:26.987 --> 00:00:28.671
Since I was very young,
我从很小的时候，

6
00:00:28.695 --> 00:00:30.879
I dreamed of working for the United Nations
就梦想在世界上

7
00:00:30.903 --> 00:00:33.879
in some of the most difficult countries in the world.
某些最困难的国家里 为联合国工作。

8
00:00:33.903 --> 00:00:36.213
And thanks to a lot of courage
凭借很大的勇气，

9
00:00:36.237 --> 00:00:38.338
that dream came true.
我的梦想成真了。

10
00:00:38.362 --> 00:00:40.379
But here's the thing about courage:
但关于勇气的问题是：

11
00:00:40.403 --> 00:00:43.004
it doesn't just appear whenever we need it.
它并不会在我们需要它 的时候凭空出现。

12
00:00:43.028 --> 00:00:46.338
It's the result of tough reflection and real work,
它是坚韧不移的反思 和脚踏实地的努力的结果，

13
00:00:46.362 --> 00:00:50.838
involving the balance between fear and bravery.
需要恐惧和勇敢之间的平衡。

14
00:00:50.862 --> 00:00:53.671
Without fear, we'll do foolish things.
没有恐惧，我们会做蠢事。

15
00:00:53.695 --> 00:00:57.713
And without courage, we'll never step into the unknown.
而没有勇气， 我们永远不会朝未知迈步。

16
00:00:57.737 --> 00:01:00.588
The balance of the two is where the magic lies,
两者的平衡 正是魔法诞生的地方，

17
00:01:00.612 --> 00:01:03.653
and it's a balance we all deal with every day.
而这是一种我们所有人 每天都要面对的平衡。

18
00:01:04.778 --> 00:01:07.213
First, a word about my fancy wheels.
首先，让我讲讲我的神奇轮椅。

19
00:01:07.237 --> 00:01:09.296
I haven't always used a wheelchair.
我并不是一直坐轮椅的。

20
00:01:09.320 --> 00:01:10.796
I grew up like many of you,
我像你们很多人一样，

21
00:01:10.820 --> 00:01:13.004
running, jumping and dancing.
在奔跑、跳跃和舞蹈中长大。

22
00:01:13.028 --> 00:01:15.879
I love to dance.
我热爱跳舞。

23
00:01:15.903 --> 00:01:18.171
However, in my mid-twenties,
然而，在我二十多岁时，

24
00:01:18.195 --> 00:01:22.296
I began to experience a series of inexplicable falls.
我开始经历 一系列难以解释的跌倒。

25
00:01:22.320 --> 00:01:23.629
And a few years later,
几年之后，

26
00:01:23.653 --> 00:01:27.004
I was diagnosed with a recessive genetic condition
我被确诊患有 一种隐性遗传疾病，

27
00:01:27.028 --> 00:01:30.671
called hereditary inclusion body myopathy,
叫做遗传性包涵体肌炎，

28
00:01:30.695 --> 00:01:33.213
or HIBM.
简称 HIBM。

29
00:01:33.237 --> 00:01:36.046
It's a progressive muscle wasting disease
这是一种进行性的肌肉萎缩症，

30
00:01:36.070 --> 00:01:39.713
that affects all of my muscles from head to toe.
它影响到我从头到脚 的所有肌肉。

31
00:01:39.737 --> 00:01:41.879
HIBM is very rare.
HIBM 非常罕见。

32
00:01:41.903 --> 00:01:47.296
In the United States there are less than 200 people diagnosed.
在美国不到 200 人被确诊。

33
00:01:47.320 --> 00:01:51.504
To date, there is no proved treatment or cure,
至今我们都没有可靠 的治疗手段或治愈方法，

34
00:01:51.528 --> 00:01:54.588
and within 10 to 15 years of its onset,
在发作十到十五年内，

35
00:01:54.612 --> 00:01:57.504
HIBM typically leads to quadriplegia,
HIBM 通常会造成四肢瘫痪，

36
00:01:57.528 --> 00:02:00.463
which is why I now use a wheelchair.
也就是我现在坐轮椅的原因。

37
00:02:00.487 --> 00:02:04.088
When I was first diagnosed, everything changed.
我最初被确诊时， 一切都改变了。

38
00:02:04.112 --> 00:02:06.088
It was frightening news
这是很可怕的消息，

39
00:02:06.112 --> 00:02:10.463
because I had no experience with chronic illness or disabilities.
因为我没有慢性病或 身体障碍的经验。

40
00:02:10.487 --> 00:02:14.879
And I had no idea how the disease might progress.
我也完全不知道 这种病会如何发展。

41
00:02:14.903 --> 00:02:17.004
But what was most disheartening
但最让人沮丧的

42
00:02:17.028 --> 00:02:20.171
was to listen to other people advise me
是听到别人建议我

43
00:02:20.195 --> 00:02:22.338
to limit my ambitions and dreams,
抑制自己的雄心与梦想，

44
00:02:22.362 --> 00:02:26.028
and to change my expectations of what to expect from life.
改变我对人生的期望。

45
00:02:27.028 --> 00:02:29.838
"You should quit your international career."
“你应该放弃你的国际职业。”

46
00:02:29.862 --> 00:02:32.504
"No one will marry you this way."
“你这个样子没人会和你结婚。”

47
00:02:32.528 --> 00:02:35.237
"You would be selfish to have children."
“你生小孩的话就是自私。”

48
00:02:36.570 --> 00:02:38.796
The fact that someone who wasn't me
由别人而不是我自己

49
00:02:38.820 --> 00:02:41.671
was putting limitations on my dreams and ambitions
对我的梦想和志向设限

50
00:02:41.695 --> 00:02:43.463
was preposterous.
是荒谬可笑的，

51
00:02:43.487 --> 00:02:45.112
And unacceptable.
而且令人无法接受。

52
00:02:46.695 --> 00:02:47.963
So I ignored them.
所以我无视了他们。

53
00:02:47.987 --> 00:02:54.504
(Cheers and applause)
（喝彩与掌声）

54
00:02:54.528 --> 00:02:56.171
I did get married.
我结了婚。

55
00:02:56.195 --> 00:03:00.004
And I decided for myself not to have children.
我自己做出了 不要孩子的决定。

56
00:03:00.028 --> 00:03:03.338
And I continued my career with the United Nations
我在确诊后

57
00:03:01.604 --> 00:03:04.329
after my diagnosis,
仍继续留在联合国，

58
00:03:04.653 --> 00:03:07.088
going to work for two years in Angola,
在安哥拉工作了两年，

59
00:03:07.112 --> 00:03:11.028
a country recovering from 27 years of brutal civil war.
一个从 27 年残酷内战中 恢复的国家。

60
00:03:11.945 --> 00:03:13.879
However, it would be another five years
但是，又过了五年之后，

61
00:03:13.903 --> 00:03:17.713
until I officially declared my diagnosis to my employer.
我才正式把我的诊断结果 报告给我的雇主。

62
00:03:17.737 --> 00:03:19.046
Because I was afraid
因为我害怕

63
00:03:19.070 --> 00:03:23.421
that they would question my capacity to manage and I'd lose my job.
他们质疑我的应付能力， 从而让我丢掉工作。

64
00:03:23.445 --> 00:03:26.671
I was working in countries where polio had been common,
我在小儿麻痹症 曾肆虐的国家工作，

65
00:03:26.695 --> 00:03:28.463
so when I overheard someone say
所以当我听到别人说

66
00:03:28.487 --> 00:03:31.213
that they thought I might have survived polio,
他们觉得我可能是 小儿麻痹症的幸存者，

67
00:03:31.237 --> 00:03:33.838
I thought my secret was safe.
我觉得我的秘密很安全。

68
00:03:33.862 --> 00:03:36.171
No one asked why I was limping.
没有人问我为什么跛脚走路，

69
00:03:36.195 --> 00:03:38.379
So I didn't say anything.
所以我缄口不提。

70
00:03:38.403 --> 00:03:39.754
It took me over a decade
我花了十年多的时间

71
00:03:39.778 --> 00:03:42.963
to internalize the severity of HIBM,
才适应了 HIBM 的严重性，

72
00:03:42.987 --> 00:03:47.629
even as basic tasks and functions became increasingly difficult.
即使基本的动作和功能 都变得愈发困难。

73
00:03:47.653 --> 00:03:51.713
Yet, I continued to pursue my dream of working all over the world,
然而，我继续追逐我 在世界各地工作的梦想，

74
00:03:51.737 --> 00:03:54.129
and was even appointed as a disability focal point
甚至被委任为 UNICEF 在海地的

75
00:03:54.153 --> 00:03:56.046
for UNICEF in Haiti,
残疾人联络点，

76
00:03:56.070 --> 00:03:59.945
where I served for two years after the devastating 2010 earthquake.
在 2010 的破坏性大地震后， 我在那里任职两年。

77
00:04:00.820 --> 00:04:03.713
And then my work brought me to the United States.
之后我的工作 把我带到了美国。

78
00:04:03.737 --> 00:04:06.504
And even as the disease progressed significantly
即使疾病恶化得非常明显，

79
00:04:06.528 --> 00:04:09.546
and I needed leg braces and a walker to get around,
我需要腿部支架 和助步车才能出行，

80
00:04:09.570 --> 00:04:12.546
I still longed for adventure.
我依然渴望着冒险。

81
00:04:12.570 --> 00:04:13.838
And this time,
而这一次，

82
00:04:13.862 --> 00:04:17.254
I started dreaming of a grand outdoor adventure.
我开始梦想 一次宏大的户外冒险。

83
00:04:17.278 --> 00:04:20.737
And what's more grand than the Grand Canyon?
还有什么能比大峡谷更宏大？

84
00:04:21.695 --> 00:04:26.088
Did you know that for every five million people who visit the Rim
你是否知道每五百万个 造访大峡谷的人中

85
00:04:26.112 --> 00:04:29.362
only one percent go down to the canyon's base?
只有 1% 会下到 峡谷谷底？

86
00:04:30.237 --> 00:04:33.213
I wanted to be a part of that one percent.
我想成为那 1% 中的一员。

87
00:04:33.237 --> 00:04:34.754
The only thing is --
唯一的问题是——

88
00:04:34.778 --> 00:04:39.129
(Applause)
（掌声）

89
00:04:39.153 --> 00:04:43.546
The only thing is that the Grand Canyon isn't exactly accessible.
唯一的问题是 大峡谷并没有那么利于通行。

90
00:04:43.570 --> 00:04:45.296
I was going to need some assistance
要想从五千英尺 垂直而松散的地势下去，

91
00:04:45.320 --> 00:04:50.254
to get down the 5,000-foot descent of vertical loose terrain.
我得需要一些帮助。

92
00:04:50.278 --> 00:04:51.838
Now, when I face obstacles,
当我面对困难时，

93
00:04:51.862 --> 00:04:55.629
fear doesn't necessarily immediately set in
恐惧并不一定会立刻到来，

94
00:04:55.653 --> 00:04:58.463
because I assume that one way or another,
因为我觉得不管怎样，

95
00:04:57.903 --> 00:05:00.180
I'll figure it out.
我总会找到解决的办法。

96
00:05:00.070 --> 00:05:02.296
And in this case, my thought was,
而在这件事情中， 我的想法是，

97
00:05:02.320 --> 00:05:04.463
well, if I can't walk down,
如果我没法走下去，

98
00:05:04.487 --> 00:05:06.671
I could learn to ride a horse.
我可以学习骑马。

99
00:05:06.695 --> 00:05:08.629
So that's what I did.
于是我就这么做了。

100
00:05:08.653 --> 00:05:10.463
And with that fateful decision
随着这个重大决定的诞生，

101
00:05:10.487 --> 00:05:12.463
began a four-year commitment,
我投入了四年时间，

102
00:05:12.487 --> 00:05:15.546
tossing back and forth between fear and courage
在恐惧与勇气之间辗转反侧，

103
00:05:15.570 --> 00:05:18.296
to undertake a 12-day expedition.
为了进行这场为期 12 天的征途。

104
00:05:18.320 --> 00:05:21.546
Four days on horseback to cross Grand Canyon rim to rim,
四天骑马从南缘到北缘 横跨大峡谷，

105
00:05:21.570 --> 00:05:25.588
and eight days rafting 150 miles of the Colorado River,
八天划艇渡过 240 多公里的科罗拉多河，

106
00:05:25.612 --> 00:05:27.546
all with a film crew in tow.
全程由摄影组跟随。

107
00:05:27.570 --> 00:05:29.879
Spoiler alert -- we made it.
剧透警告——我们成功了。

108
00:05:29.903 --> 00:05:32.713
But not without showing me how my deepest fear
而我也见识了 我最深的恐惧

109
00:05:32.737 --> 00:05:37.588
can somehow manifest a mirror response of equal courage.
能以某种方式 对称地激发等量的勇气。

110
00:05:37.612 --> 00:05:40.796
On April 13, 2018,
2018 年 4 月 13 日，

111
00:05:40.820 --> 00:05:42.546
sitting eight feet above the ground,
坐在离地八英尺处，

112
00:05:42.570 --> 00:05:44.796
riding a mustang horse named Sheriff,
骑在名为警长的野马背上，

113
00:05:44.820 --> 00:05:47.088
my first impression of Grand Canyon
我对大峡谷的第一印象

114
00:05:47.112 --> 00:05:50.004
was one of shock and terror.
是震惊与恐怖。

115
00:05:50.028 --> 00:05:52.838
Who knew I had a fear of heights.
谁知道我会恐高呢。

116
00:05:52.862 --> 00:05:54.129
(Laughter)
（笑声）

117
00:05:54.153 --> 00:05:56.671
But there was no giving up now.
但事到如今，已经没有回头路了。

118
00:05:56.695 --> 00:06:00.421
I mustered up every ounce of courage inside me
我鼓起身体里每一丝勇气，

119
00:06:00.445 --> 00:06:03.921
to not let my fear get the best of me.
不让自己被恐惧战胜。

120
00:06:03.945 --> 00:06:05.754
Embarking on the South Rim,
从大峡谷南崖出发，

121
00:06:05.778 --> 00:06:08.504
all I could do to keep myself composed
我让自己保持镇定的方法

122
00:06:08.528 --> 00:06:12.171
was to breathe deeply, stare up into the clouds
唯有深呼吸， 抬头望云，

123
00:06:12.195 --> 00:06:15.713
and focus on my team's voices.
以及把注意力集中到 队友的声音上。

124
00:06:15.737 --> 00:06:20.296
But then, in the first hour, disaster struck.
然而在第一个小时内， 灾难就降临了。

125
00:06:20.320 --> 00:06:22.671
Unable to hold myself upright in the saddle,
我在下一大步台阶时

126
00:06:22.695 --> 00:06:24.671
going down an oversized step,
没法在马鞍上保持直立，

127
00:06:24.695 --> 00:06:29.213
I flung forward and smacked my face on the back of the horse's head.
向前一扑， 脸砸在了马的后脑勺上。

128
00:06:29.237 --> 00:06:30.504
There was panic,
现场变得慌乱，

129
00:06:30.528 --> 00:06:32.088
my head hurt fiercely,
我的头剧烈疼痛，

130
00:06:32.112 --> 00:06:35.796
but the path was too narrow for us to dismount.
但山路过于狭窄， 我们无法下马。

131
00:06:35.820 --> 00:06:38.629
Only at the halfway point at 2,300 feet,
直到 700 米处的中途休息点，

132
00:06:38.653 --> 00:06:40.879
at least another two hours down,
此时至少又走了两个小时下坡路，

133
00:06:40.903 --> 00:06:43.004
could we stop and remove my helmet
我们才能停下来，摘下我的头盔，

134
00:06:43.028 --> 00:06:46.963
and see the egg-sized bump protruding from my forehead.
看到我的额头凸出的 鸡蛋大小的肿包。

135
00:06:46.987 --> 00:06:49.046
For all of that planning and gear,
看看我们这么充分的准备与装备

136
00:06:49.070 --> 00:06:51.879
how is it that we didn't even have an ice pack?
怎么现在连冰袋都没有？

137
00:06:51.903 --> 00:06:52.921
(Laughter)
（笑声）

138
00:06:52.945 --> 00:06:55.838
Luckily for all of us, the swelling came outwards,
所幸的是， 肿胀向外扩散，

139
00:06:55.862 --> 00:06:59.879
and would drain into my face as two fantastic black eyes
之后淤血朝脸上排出， 形成两只绝妙的黑眼圈，

140
00:06:59.903 --> 00:07:02.963
which is an amazing way to look in a documentary film.
在纪录片里是 无比神奇的妆容。

141
00:07:02.987 --> 00:07:05.046
(Laughter)
（笑声）

142
00:07:05.070 --> 00:07:10.129
(Applause and cheers)
（鼓掌与喝彩）

143
00:07:10.153 --> 00:07:12.296
This was not an easy, peaceful journey,
这并非一段轻松平稳的旅程，

144
00:07:12.320 --> 00:07:14.379
and yet, that was exactly the point.
然而这一点恰恰是最重要的。

145
00:07:14.403 --> 00:07:17.004
Even though I was afraid to get back into the saddle,
尽管我害怕重新坐上马鞍，

146
00:07:17.028 --> 00:07:18.379
I got back in.
我还是上了马。

147
00:07:18.403 --> 00:07:20.754
The descent alone to the canyon floor
下到峡谷谷底的路程

148
00:07:20.778 --> 00:07:22.671
took a total of 10 hours
就花了总共 10 个小时，

149
00:07:22.695 --> 00:07:25.588
and that was just day one of four riding.
这还只是骑马的四天中的一天。

150
00:07:25.612 --> 00:07:27.671
Next came the mighty rapids.
接下来是强大的急流。

151
00:07:27.695 --> 00:07:29.671
The Colorado River in the Grand Canyon
大峡谷中的科罗拉多河

152
00:07:29.695 --> 00:07:32.588
has some of the highest white water in the country.
有高度位居全国前列的白浪。

153
00:07:32.612 --> 00:07:35.463
And just to be prepared in case we should capsize,
以防万一我们翻船，

154
00:07:35.487 --> 00:07:38.296
we'd practice having me swim through a smaller rapid.
大家练习让我游过一处小型激流。

155
00:07:38.320 --> 00:07:41.004
And it's safe to say it wasn't glamorous.
我可以不夸张地说， 这毫无魅力可言。

156
00:07:41.028 --> 00:07:42.088
(Laughter)
（笑声）

157
00:07:42.112 --> 00:07:44.629
I took my breath in the wrong part of the wave,
我在浪里错误的位置换气，

158
00:07:44.653 --> 00:07:46.088
choked on river water
被河水呛到，

159
00:07:46.112 --> 00:07:48.629
and was unable to steer myself.
没法操纵自己的方向。

160
00:07:48.653 --> 00:07:50.213
Yes, it was scary,
没错，很吓人，

161
00:07:50.237 --> 00:07:52.629
but it was also fantastic.
但同时也很美妙。

162
00:07:52.653 --> 00:07:54.796
Waterfalls, slick canyons
瀑布，光滑的峡谷，

163
00:07:54.820 --> 00:07:56.754
and a couple billion years of bedrock
历经数十亿年光阴的基岩

164
00:07:56.778 --> 00:07:59.254
that seemed to change color throughout the day.
似乎随着一天内时间 的流逝改变色彩。

165
00:07:59.278 --> 00:08:02.171
The Grand Canyon is true wilderness
大峡谷是真正的旷野，

166
00:08:02.195 --> 00:08:04.879
and worthy of all of its accolades.
当得起所有对它的赞誉。

167
00:08:04.903 --> 00:08:08.612
(Applause)
（掌声）

168
00:08:12.653 --> 00:08:14.046
The expedition,
这次探险，

169
00:08:14.070 --> 00:08:17.004
all that planning and the trip itself,
所有的筹备和旅途本身

170
00:08:17.028 --> 00:08:22.046
showed me a level of fear I had never experienced before.
向我展现了之前 从未体验过的恐惧。

171
00:08:22.070 --> 00:08:23.463
But more importantly,
但更重要的是，

172
00:08:23.487 --> 00:08:27.879
it showed me how boldly courageous I can be.
它也向我展现了 我能有怎样的胆量和勇气。

173
00:08:27.903 --> 00:08:30.171
My Grand Canyon journey was not easy.
我的大峡谷之旅并不容易。

174
00:08:30.195 --> 00:08:32.838
This was not a vision of an Amazonian woman
这并不是一位亚马逊女战士

175
00:08:32.862 --> 00:08:36.379
effortlessly making her way through epic scenery.
毫不费力地穿过 史诗般景色的图景。

176
00:08:36.403 --> 00:08:38.088
This was me crying,
这是一个哭着的我，

177
00:08:38.112 --> 00:08:42.004
exhausted and beat up with two black eyes.
筋疲力尽，鼻青脸肿地 顶着两只黑眼圈。

178
00:08:42.028 --> 00:08:43.421
It was scary,
这趟旅程是可怕的，

179
00:08:43.445 --> 00:08:45.421
it was stressful,
是充满压力的，

180
00:08:45.445 --> 00:08:47.737
it was exhilarating.
也是令人振奋的。

181
00:08:48.820 --> 00:08:50.088
Now that the trip is over,
如今旅程已经结束，

182
00:08:50.112 --> 00:08:53.629
it's easy to be blasé about what we achieved.
很容易对我们的成就轻描淡写。

183
00:08:53.653 --> 00:08:56.171
I know I want to raft the river again.
我知道我还想划艇渡河，

184
00:08:56.195 --> 00:08:59.588
This time, all 277 miles of it.
这次，划完全程 445 公里。

185
00:08:59.612 --> 00:09:03.046
(Applause)
（掌声）

186
00:09:03.070 --> 00:09:06.421
But I also know that I would never do the horseback-riding part again.
但我也知道我再也不会 重复一遍骑马的部分了。

187
00:09:06.445 --> 00:09:08.088
(Laughter)
（笑声）

188
00:09:08.112 --> 00:09:10.671
It's just too dangerous.
实在是太危险了。

189
00:09:10.695 --> 00:09:12.338
And that's my real point.
而那是我真正想说的。

190
00:09:12.362 --> 00:09:15.254
I'm not just here to show you my film footage.
我在这里并不只是 向各位展示我的影像片段。

191
00:09:15.278 --> 00:09:17.296
I'm here to remind us all
我在这里是想提醒大家，

192
00:09:17.320 --> 00:09:19.546
that life is really just a lesson
人生其实就是一堂课，

193
00:09:19.570 --> 00:09:22.629
in finding the balance between fear and courage.
教我们如何寻找 恐惧与勇气之间的平衡，

194
00:09:22.653 --> 00:09:27.463
And understanding what is and what isn't a good idea.
以及理解什么是好主意， 什么并非是好主意。

195
00:09:27.487 --> 00:09:28.713
(Laughter)
（笑声）

196
00:09:28.737 --> 00:09:30.463
Life is already scary,
生活已经很可怕了，

197
00:09:30.487 --> 00:09:34.213
so for our dreams to come true, we need to be brave.
所以为了实现我们的梦想， 我们必须要勇敢。

198
00:09:34.237 --> 00:09:35.588
In facing my fears
通过直面我的恐惧

199
00:09:35.612 --> 00:09:38.213
and finding the courage to push through them,
并找到克服它们的勇气，

200
00:09:38.237 --> 00:09:41.921
I swear my life has been extraordinary.
我可以发誓，我的人生非常精彩。

201
00:09:41.945 --> 00:09:43.379
So live big
所以生活要有大目标，

202
00:09:43.403 --> 00:09:46.338
and try to let your courage outweigh your fear.
努力让你的勇气 战胜你的恐惧。

203
00:09:46.362 --> 00:09:49.296
You never know where it might take you.
你永远也不会知道 它会将你带向何方。

204
00:09:49.320 --> 00:09:50.588
Thank you.
谢谢大家。

205
00:09:50.612 --> 00:09:54.070
(Applause and cheers)
（掌声与喝彩）